and twice during gastro spasm.

249
00:15:52,671 --> 00:15:55,001
He was administered total
of four times during two months.

250
00:15:55,101 --> 00:15:56,576
There wasn't any before or after.

251
00:15:56,666 --> 00:15:59,479
FAMA who was cleared of taking propofol

252
00:15:59,570 --> 00:16:04,070
stated that he will be even more
devoted to his music career in the future.

253
00:16:04,469 --> 00:16:06,467
This is Yoon Yoo-Rae from YGN news.

254
00:16:12,439 --> 00:16:15,085
These kinds of issue should last
few more days,

255
00:16:15,649 --> 00:16:17,326
but the YGN's report was so fast

256
00:16:17,685 --> 00:16:20,276
that it was inadequate to cover it up.

257
00:16:28,119 --> 00:16:29,261
I'm sure it was.

258
00:16:29,352 --> 00:16:32,513
You work so hard and
have a lot of connections.

259
00:16:32,622 --> 00:16:35,382
The reporters at the parking lot
was just a coincidence

260
00:16:35,473 --> 00:16:36,893
and the rumor was probably wrong.

261
00:16:36,984 --> 00:16:40,924
Since you are both so competent!

262
00:16:50,022 --> 00:16:51,425
Yes, Assemblyman Joo.

263
00:16:53,612 --> 00:16:54,954
Don't mention it.

264
00:16:56,502 --> 00:16:57,340
Of course.

265
00:16:58,649 --> 00:17:00,731
I know it's a sensitive time.

266
00:17:02,591 --> 00:17:06,253
You don't have to worry.
Just think of as a passing wind.

267
00:17:08,872 --> 00:17:11,033
You remember the date of
the grand opening ceremony, right?

268
00:17:12,902 --> 00:17:14,176
Of course we'll stay on schedule.

269
00:17:15,060 --> 00:17:15,981
Then...

270
00:17:16,810 --> 00:17:18,439
Yes. I'll see you then.

271
00:17:21,707 --> 00:17:25,369
So tell me. What should I try this time?

272
00:17:26,932 --> 00:17:28,013
Ma'am.

273
00:17:28,296 --> 00:17:31,225
Defamation of character falls through
more than half of the time.

274
00:17:31,592 --> 00:17:35,917
If the victim doesn't want you
to be punished, you can't be punished.

275
00:17:36,845 --> 00:17:37,603
So...

276
00:17:38,714 --> 00:17:41,752
are you saying that I should go see
Officer Ahn and beg?

277
00:17:41,852 --> 00:17:43,476
Rather than begging,

278
00:17:43,576 --> 00:17:45,761
won't it be better to resolve
the misunderstanding quickly?

279
00:17:46,574 --> 00:17:48,140
Before the matter gets any bigger,

280
00:17:48,230 --> 00:17:50,500
it'd be better to reach
an agreement with Officer Ahn

281
00:17:50,620 --> 00:17:52,471
and quietly settle it.

282
00:17:53,348 --> 00:17:54,970
If it turns out like this,

283
00:17:55,334 --> 00:17:58,064
Chairwoman Park will change
the direction to appease Officer Ahn.

284
00:17:58,703 --> 00:18:00,040
Appease him?

285
00:18:01,590 --> 00:18:03,649
Defamation of character fails
more than half of the time.

286
00:18:03,740 --> 00:18:04,960
That's right.

287
00:18:05,451 --> 00:18:09,455
If Officer Ahn reaches an agreement,
Chairwoman Park won't be punished.

288
00:18:09,546 --> 00:18:13,607
Then this case will just end like this.

289
00:18:14,517 --> 00:18:19,525
Her side will probably try to convince
Officer Ahn with favorable conditions.

290
00:18:20,093 --> 00:18:23,375
If he falls for that appeasement,
everything will go up in the air.

291
00:18:23,884 --> 00:18:25,218
What do you think?

292
00:18:25,318 --> 00:18:28,230
Is he a person who will fall for
something like that?

293
00:18:28,818 --> 00:18:29,691
No.

294
00:18:35,108 --> 00:18:36,463
I don't know.

295
00:18:36,827 --> 00:18:38,807
He has three kids.

296
00:18:44,387 --> 00:18:45,877
Hey.

297
00:18:45,967 --> 00:18:49,679
Even if I have three kids,
I'm a proud Police officer of Korea.

298
00:18:49,779 --> 00:18:52,096
I will never fall for an appeasement.
I won't settle.

299
00:18:52,196 --> 00:18:55,036
I knew that you'd be like this.
I believed in you.

300
00:19:00,211 --> 00:19:02,946
I was a little bit doubtful.
Just a little bit.

301
00:19:07,112 --> 00:19:09,173
Fine. I was really doubtful.

302
00:19:09,922 --> 00:19:10,818
I'm sorry.

303
00:19:12,832 --> 00:19:14,961
You were worried that Chan-soo
will fall for it. Right?

304
00:19:15,316 --> 00:19:16,264
No. Not at all.

305
00:19:16,874 --> 00:19:17,583
Hey!

306
00:19:19,413 --> 00:19:20,468
Don't worry.

307
00:19:21,361 --> 00:19:23,116
I started this fight because of you,
Ha-myung.

308
00:19:23,796 --> 00:19:26,597
I started this because I was sorry for
spreading that rumor in high school

309
00:19:26,689 --> 00:19:28,800
and because you saved me
despite all that.

310
00:19:28,891 --> 00:19:32,006
I started this because you told me to
and I'll stop when you tell me to stop.

311
00:19:34,557 --> 00:19:36,300
I know what this fight means to you.

312
00:19:37,625 --> 00:19:40,833
I'm going to stake my conscience
and hold out to the end.

313
00:19:42,304 --> 00:19:43,408
Thanks, Chan-soo.

314
00:19:44,918 --> 00:19:48,617
If you're that thankful, bring a gift to
my housewarming party this weekend.

315
00:19:49,162 --> 00:19:50,247
A housewarming party?

316
00:19:50,463 --> 00:19:52,348
I thought it's been three years
since you moved.

317
00:19:52,448 --> 00:19:53,848
So why are you having
a housewarming party?

318
00:19:54,378 --> 00:19:57,380
It's been three years but it hasn't been
that long since I met you guys again.

319
00:19:59,258 --> 00:20:01,964
Come with light hearts
but heavy hands okay?

320
00:20:02,064 --> 00:20:05,186
It wasn't enough that you had
a first birthday party for your third kid?

321
00:20:05,638 --> 00:20:07,346
You really don't have any conscience.

322
00:20:07,490 --> 00:20:09,205
You try having three
kids and raising them.

323
00:20:09,296 --> 00:20:10,532
Things like conscience are a luxury.

324
00:20:14,060 --> 00:20:14,992
Hey.

325
00:20:15,361 --> 00:20:17,066
You said you're putting
your conscience on the line?

326
00:20:18,954 --> 00:20:22,882
That conscience and this conscience are
managed separately so don't worry.

327
00:20:35,636 --> 00:20:37,309
I'm back.

328
00:20:42,262 --> 00:20:44,972
You're just coming home?
Wash up quickly and let's eat.

329
00:20:45,244 --> 00:20:46,821
Why are you coming out of that room,
grandpa?

330
00:20:47,882 --> 00:20:51,078
I went to your brother's house
and brought back some clothes.

331
00:20:51,472 --> 00:20:55,160
I put them in the dresser so wear them.

332
00:20:57,266 --> 00:21:01,657
Even if we're home, I couldn't stand
watching you wearing my short clothes.

333
00:21:02,666 --> 00:21:04,072
I could've gotten them myself.

334
00:21:04,172 --> 00:21:06,622
How nice would it be if you could
fit into anyone's clothes?

335
00:21:06,722 --> 00:21:08,828
Your limbs are uselessly long.

336
00:21:09,149 --> 00:21:09,882
He's right.

337
00:21:09,982 --> 00:21:13,250
You are longer than you need to be.

338
00:21:27,262 --> 00:21:29,834
By the way, will Chan-soo be alright?

339
00:21:30,122 --> 00:21:31,678
Why? Are you nervous?

340
00:21:31,852 --> 00:21:35,222
No but Chairwoman Park is going to
suggest something enormous.

341
00:21:35,332 --> 00:21:38,242
If Chan-soo agrees to settle,
everything will end right here.

342
00:21:39,302 --> 00:21:41,828
Don't worry. Chan-soo isn't someone
who would fall for that.

343
00:21:42,082 --> 00:21:45,107
And Nitpicker is supposed to be there
tomorrow so you don't need to worry.

344
00:21:46,093 --> 00:21:48,142
Then it's a relief. Then wash up.

345
00:21:48,262 --> 00:21:48,867
Yeah.

346
00:21:58,676 --> 00:22:00,573
That's right.
Call me when you need to shave.

347
00:22:02,802 --> 00:22:04,191
Hey, your right arm.

348
00:22:07,812 --> 00:22:10,073
What is this? Are you fine now?

349
00:22:14,401 --> 00:22:15,481
What is this?

350
00:22:15,681 --> 00:22:17,794
Why were you pretending your arm
hurt when it was healed?

351
00:22:18,391 --> 00:22:22,101
I wasn't pretending.
It's not completely well yet.

352
00:22:23,811 --> 00:22:24,405
Why?

353
00:22:24,869 --> 00:22:27,304
Were you worried that we'd tell
you to go home if you're better?

354
00:22:27,991 --> 00:22:29,599
No. It's...

355
00:22:30,701 --> 00:22:32,202
You like this house, don't you?

356
00:22:32,791 --> 00:22:36,141
You don't have to eat
those flimsy fried eggs here

357
00:22:36,241 --> 00:22:38,625
and you can see grandpa
and my father everyday.

358
00:22:39,491 --> 00:22:41,314
And you can see me everyday too, right?

359
00:22:43,761 --> 00:22:45,555
Can't you just move back in?

360
00:22:46,171 --> 00:22:48,788
Are you still worried
about your brother a lot?

361
00:22:50,301 --> 00:22:51,371
No.

362
00:22:53,791 --> 00:22:55,237
Then move back in.

363
00:22:55,871 --> 00:22:59,266
I've been worried
about that ridiculous breakfast.

364
00:23:00,751 --> 00:23:03,401
- Come out and eat.
- Yes.

365
00:23:03,501 --> 00:23:04,661
Hurry up and come out.

366
00:23:05,871 --> 00:23:06,976
Throw this away.

367
00:23:29,921 --> 00:23:32,811
- What is this?
- What in the world...

368
00:23:33,121 --> 00:23:35,848
The Chairwoman would like
to resolve the misunderstanding.

369
00:23:36,141 --> 00:23:37,139
Take them back.

370
00:23:37,997 --> 00:23:40,231
If it's a misunderstanding,
doesn't it mean that she won't admit it?

371
00:23:41,881 --> 00:23:43,077
First...

372
00:23:44,421 --> 00:23:46,662
...you should resolve
the misunderstanding.

373
00:23:48,651 --> 00:23:49,938
Look here.

374
00:23:54,705 --> 00:23:56,851
- How much is this?
- How much is it?

375
00:23:56,961 --> 00:23:58,285
How much is it?

376
00:24:08,621 --> 00:24:11,603
- Aren't they Chairman Park's people?
- I think you're right.

377
00:24:11,703 --> 00:24:13,143
Hey!

378
00:24:13,243 --> 00:24:15,293
Are you here to have him agree
to a settlement?

379
00:24:15,393 --> 00:24:16,803
What is all this?

380
00:24:16,903 --> 00:24:18,873
What is that envelope?

381
00:24:26,443 --> 00:24:28,833
What I need isn't an envelope
full of money or settlement.

382
00:24:29,673 --> 00:24:33,107
I'm a proud police officer of Korea.
Tell Chairwoman Park clearly.

383
00:24:33,198 --> 00:24:35,620
I, Ahn Chan-soo,
don't need things like these.

384
00:24:37,092 --> 00:24:38,264
Please tell us one thing.

385
00:24:48,427 --> 00:24:50,217
He said that he doesn't need anything.

386
00:24:50,308 --> 00:24:53,464
So he'd like you to admit to the charge
and come to apologize personally.

387
00:24:53,837 --> 00:24:56,397
- That's what he said.
- And?

388
00:24:56,603 --> 00:24:57,526
That was...

389
00:24:59,174 --> 00:25:00,123
That was all.

390
00:25:01,778 --> 00:25:03,582
Is that all?

391
00:25:03,977 --> 00:25:06,583
Then I just have to go and apologize?

392
00:25:06,683 --> 00:25:10,293
I should've gone myself.
I've committed a grave sin.

393
00:25:10,393 --> 00:25:13,005
What do I have to do?
Do I just have to kneel and beg?

394
00:25:13,105 --> 00:25:14,570
Should I beg like this?

395
00:25:14,670 --> 00:25:16,054
- Ma'am.
- What?

396
00:25:16,145 --> 00:25:17,954
I don't think there is any other way.

397
00:25:18,214 --> 00:25:20,740
You must cooperate with
the investigation at this point

398
00:25:20,840 --> 00:25:22,661
and look for a different way out.

399
00:25:22,771 --> 00:25:24,223
Team Leader. Secretary Ko.

400
00:25:24,666 --> 00:25:27,193
Am I not giving you enough money?

401
00:25:27,501 --> 00:25:28,164
Am I?

402
00:25:29,128 --> 00:25:32,411
Tell me if you need more money,
instead of doing things like this.

403
00:25:32,589 --> 00:25:36,051
Ma'am. Just bend down for a bit
and plan out future affairs.

404
00:25:36,151 --> 00:25:38,351
Bend down? To whom?

405
00:25:38,681 --> 00:25:39,915
To that police officer?

406
00:25:40,884 --> 00:25:43,018
Then it would mean that
I'm admitting to defamation of character.

407
00:25:43,351 --> 00:25:45,212
And I'm admitting those connections.

408
00:25:45,303 --> 00:25:47,864
They'll reveal all the assemblymen
to the world

409
00:25:47,955 --> 00:25:50,422
and the prosecution will start
the internal investigation.

410
00:25:50,513 --> 00:25:52,550
Do you think this will end
with just bending down a little?

411
00:25:52,787 --> 00:25:53,783
Really?

412
00:26:05,721 --> 00:26:07,213
Now let's do it my way.

413
00:26:08,945 --> 00:26:11,481
- Excuse me?
- The rougher you are to them...

414
00:26:13,688 --> 00:26:16,254
the nicer they are to you.

415
00:26:18,119 --> 00:26:19,627
Let's take the easy way now.

416
00:26:20,075 --> 00:26:22,331
We've done enough to humor them
and pacify them.

417
00:26:23,438 --> 00:26:24,637
Let's look for another way.

418
00:26:26,141 --> 00:26:27,461
You know what I mean, don't you?

419
00:26:28,097 --> 00:26:28,989
Mother...

420
00:26:31,817 --> 00:26:33,035
Please...

421
00:26:37,551 --> 00:26:38,569
Please stop.

422
00:26:45,746 --> 00:26:46,927
Notice

423
00:26:47,027 --> 00:26:49,403
HR meeting to set punishment
for Chief Song

424
00:26:49,494 --> 00:26:51,835
I guess they want to see her to the end.

425
00:26:53,263 --> 00:26:57,330
- Is this the end of Ms Song?
- Isn't that reasonable?

426
00:26:58,283 --> 00:27:02,019
Because of her, people lost confidence
in MSC and our status has hit the ground.

427
00:27:02,750 --> 00:27:06,600
She caused this huge act of destruction,
so it's fair that she's being punished.

428
00:27:07,901 --> 00:27:11,846
I'm so displeased with you.
You're really displeasing.

429
00:27:13,086 --> 00:27:16,712
Hey, do we have to put our hands down
and just watch?

430
00:27:37,619 --> 00:27:38,839
What?

431
00:27:39,549 --> 00:27:40,971
No. It's nothing.

432
00:27:43,419 --> 00:27:46,707
But it's the first time
I'm seeing you sleep at work, mom.

433
00:27:48,772 --> 00:27:50,387
I know. It's the first time.

434
00:27:52,494 --> 00:27:54,450
You're not sick anywhere, are you?

435
00:27:55,248 --> 00:27:56,616
I'm sleepy.

436
00:27:57,569 --> 00:28:01,138
Because of insomnia, I haven't slept well
for the past 15 years.

437
00:28:02,195 --> 00:28:06,031
It seems like I'm catching up all at once.

438
00:28:08,854 --> 00:28:11,396
I saw the notice about the HR meeting.

439
00:28:13,702 --> 00:28:15,233
Yeah, I saw it too.

440
00:28:16,502 --> 00:28:18,182
I'm not surprised.

441
00:28:18,282 --> 00:28:20,172
It's rather late.

442
00:28:24,982 --> 00:28:27,658
I'm sleepy so please be quiet.

443
00:28:28,830 --> 00:28:29,892
Okay.

444
00:28:36,160 --> 00:28:38,372
I'm going to sleep just for five minutes
so stay there.

445
00:28:39,263 --> 00:28:40,784
The sun is too bright.

446
00:28:42,761 --> 00:28:43,741
Yes, mom.

447
00:29:28,790 --> 00:29:30,042
There you are.

448
00:29:31,051 --> 00:29:33,592
- Why? Were you looking for me?
- Yeah.

449
00:29:35,987 --> 00:29:37,174
I heard it all.

450
00:29:37,947 --> 00:29:40,453
I heard that your mom is called
for an HR meeting.

451
00:29:41,782 --> 00:29:43,599
You guys heard it too?

452
00:29:46,372 --> 00:29:47,316
Is it okay?

453
00:29:48,723 --> 00:29:50,177
She's seemed calmer than I thought.

454
00:29:50,287 --> 00:29:51,761
She looked somewhat peaceful.

455
00:29:51,852 --> 00:29:54,269
No. I meant you.

456
00:29:54,379 --> 00:29:55,589
Me?

457
00:29:56,319 --> 00:29:58,718
I'm fine compared to my mom.

458
00:29:59,799 --> 00:30:03,125
Other than being marked by
the new captain, it's okay. It's bearable.

459
00:30:04,519 --> 00:30:07,408
If I'm having hard time with this,
I'd feel sorry to my mom.

460
00:30:08,239 --> 00:30:10,343
Pretending you're okay
because you feel sorry,

461
00:30:11,269 --> 00:30:12,594
that's a foolish thing to do.

462
00:30:13,549 --> 00:30:15,460
No. I'm really fine.

463
00:30:19,569 --> 00:30:20,967
I guess I'm not.

464
00:30:22,859 --> 00:30:23,897
See?

465
00:30:31,969 --> 00:30:34,279
I should've held you like this then.

466
00:30:36,177 --> 00:30:38,913
Even when you told me not to worry,
comfort you or do anything,

467
00:30:40,309 --> 00:30:41,540
I should've held you anyway.

468
00:30:42,369 --> 00:30:44,030
It's so comforting.

469
00:31:11,906 --> 00:31:13,841
YGN

470
00:31:20,900 --> 00:31:22,579
You remember
the housewarming party today right?

471
00:31:22,670 --> 00:31:24,361
Light heart and heavy hands!

472
00:31:24,452 --> 00:31:25,883
Make sure to bring Reporter Yoon.

473
00:31:28,120 --> 00:31:30,850
Yoon Yoo-Rae, you're coming to Chan-soo's
housewarming party, right?

474
00:31:30,950 --> 00:31:32,500
Yeah. Why?

475
00:31:32,820 --> 00:31:34,888
Let's get together with In-ha
and go together.

476
00:31:35,980 --> 00:31:38,370
Why? Why do I have to go with you?

477
00:31:38,470 --> 00:31:40,533
Why do I have to go with someone
who has a girlfriend?

478
00:31:41,730 --> 00:31:44,403
Do you have some kind of grudge
against me these days?

479
00:31:44,780 --> 00:31:45,830
Yeah.

480
00:31:45,930 --> 00:31:48,947
You're becoming more unlikable recently.

481
00:31:49,920 --> 00:31:51,160
Fine.

482
00:31:51,250 --> 00:31:54,266
- Are you going by yourself?
- No. I'm not going by myself.

483
00:31:57,554 --> 00:31:59,930
Cha Woo-chul, wanna to go to
Officer Ahn's housewarming party?

484
00:32:00,030 --> 00:32:00,936
I'm busy.

485
00:32:04,309 --> 00:32:06,511
Captain. Do you want to go to
Officer Ahn's housewarming party?

486
00:32:06,602 --> 00:32:08,192
- Okay.
- Excuse me?

487
00:32:09,624 --> 00:32:10,656
What do you mean okay?

488
00:32:13,159 --> 00:32:14,626
You asked me to go to
the housewarming party.

489
00:32:18,531 --> 00:32:19,476
I'm going.

490
00:32:23,837 --> 00:32:25,803
Why is the captain like that?
Why is he going?

491
00:32:26,414 --> 00:32:28,134
He's going because you asked him to go.

492
00:32:29,185 --> 00:32:30,595
So why...

493
00:32:32,241 --> 00:32:33,361
I want to ask you.

494
00:32:33,729 --> 00:32:35,433
Why did you invite the captain?

495
00:32:38,102 --> 00:32:39,805
I didn't know he was going to say yes.

496
00:32:52,731 --> 00:32:54,683
What is this? Why did your captain come?

497
00:32:55,704 --> 00:32:57,925
I want to ask why he came also.

498
00:33:04,950 --> 00:33:07,731
How much did Chairwoman Park's people
talk for settlement money?

499
00:33:08,502 --> 00:33:09,951
From what I saw in the envelope,

500
00:33:10,051 --> 00:33:11,983
it seemed enough to pay off rent

501
00:33:12,083 --> 00:33:15,273
and send our kids
to a private kindergarten.

